column2: 1. What gender is your English teacher?
column4: 3. Is your English teacher's gender the same as your gender?
column5: 4. On a 7-period day, is your English class before or after lunch?
column6: 5. What high school year are you in?
column8: 7. What is your exact grade in the class? (to the hundredths place, for example 86.41%)
column9: 8. What is your cumulative GPA so far? (to the hundredths place, for example 3.37. If you are a freshman, type in 0.00)
column10: 9. How many absences do you have in English class for the semester?
column11: 10. Does your teacher use standards based grading? (Standards based grading is when 85% and above is considered an A and your teacher grades you from 1-4 on assignments)
column12: 11. How often do you have homework?
column13: 12. Do you keep up with your homework and turn assignments in on time?
column14: 13. How often do you work with groups/friends? (this is not asking about group projects, it's about who you generally do your work with)
column15: 14. What is the phone policy like in your class?
column16: 15. How often do you have group projects?
column17: 16. How many books have you read this semester in English class?
column18: 17. How many essays have you written for English so far?
column19: 18. Do you sit in a seating chart?
column20: 19. What do you sit in? (Desks that are pushed together to form partners count as desks)
column21: 20. What is the usual level of noise in your classroom?
column22: 21. How many students are in your class?
column24: 23. Does your teacher perform binder checks?
column25: 24. What is your teacher's late work policy?
column26: 25. Has there been a student teacher or teacher's assistant in your classroom this semester?
column27: 26. Do students need to raise their hands to talk?
column28: 27. How often do you usually talk in English class?
column29: 28. Are hats or hoods allowed to be worn in the classroom?
column30: 29. Is there a class pet in your classroom? (This includes animals you cannot touch, like snakes.)
column31: 30. Does your teacher keep the lights on full brightness or do they dim them in the classroom?
column33: 32. Do you enjoy your English class?
column34: 33. How strict is your English teacher with grading?
column35: 34. How much homework does your English teacher give you?
column36: 35. Does your teacher allow you to eat food whenever you want to? (besides during tests)
column37: 36. Does your teacher provide students with snacks?
column38: 37. How is the temperature of the room most of the time?
column39: 38. How often do you read books outside of class? (comics included)
column40: 39. Do one of your parents/guardians have a degree?
column41: 40. Are you the youngest, middle, or oldest sibling in your family?
column42: 41. What is your current level of happiness in general?
column43: 42. How many hours of sleep do you usually get each night?
column44: 43. What statement best describes your family's income?
